caption: Fantastic Mexican food and the owners are so nice, I love this place

Y’all when I tell you these tacos were amazing?! They were SOOO GOOD !! I don’t even normally like tomatoes and onions but this combination on the steak tacos was just out of this world. Flavorful and the spicy sauce is great if you reallly reallllllyy love spicy lol This will definitely be my regular taco place 😂🧡 The price was affordable and the food was filling 😍 Do It!
Delicious tacos and guacamole!

Hidden gem in Hamilton Heights. The storefront is a little below street/eye level so it's easy to miss amongst the bigger spots on the street. Friendly staff. The bistec burrito is amazing. Flavorful foods. Support small businesses!
The food was delicious.The delivery was fast .The  food was well presented very nice ,fresh ingredients. Hot when it arrived.This will be my new Mexican destination for sure ❤️
(Translated by Google) Excellent fast service and delicious food  (Original) Exelente servicio rápido y la comida deliciosa

My favorite Mexican spot in the city, everything tastes flavorful, fresh, and made with pride and love. The owners are from Puebla so everything is done in a poblano style. Highly recommend any burrito, the crispy tacos and the pozole blanco.
Very good tacos

Good Fish tacos are hard to come by, but Frijolito’s fish tacos are bomb! Simple pickup ordering here. Staff inside value patronage and good service to community members, looking forward to going back!

This place is fantastic. I was set with another Mexican place nearby as my go-to, but decided to try this place out from a recommendation. The tacos are fantastic. The meat is extremely flavorful, they don’t overload it with raw onion, and their toppings are fresh. The crispy taco shells are so light, airy, and fried to perfection, yet not at all greasy. Upon arrival, the tacos were still intact and warm, not soggy. They also delivered within 15 minutes the first time I ordered! They are the nicest people on the phone, too. I wish I could give this place more than 5 stars!
The carnitas were absolutely packed with flavor. From the front the store looks unassuming and I'm glad I went in.
I had the best tacos ever!! The food is amazing and customer service is excellent 👌
All of the food at Frijolito’s is excellent, but the crispy tacos are absolute perfection!
Very clean and convenient restaurant. They serve big meals and for affordable rates. I enjoyed the menu a lot and the staff were super personal and informative. I recommend this place.
Best burrito in Manhattan
Spectacular service and great food. Extremely small outside eating area but cozy. Don't bring 15 guest.....some might be eating in the street
easy pickup
Amazing Food! Been a regular over the past year
This place never fails to deliver. They have great food for convenient pricing, there is no waiting time even when the place is full.

I loved the food, the only issue is the space, it's very small, it's much better to eat outside or take out, there's sitting outside, at warmer weather it's better. Nice people and friendly manner. :) Will go again

Chios and guac are great and Tacos are fantastic. Both soft and hard shells are authentic and the seasoning of the meat is so flavorful. (Also the spicy sauce on the tacos isn't too spicy so give it a try)! Great service as well! Limited seating but perfect for a quick bite.

The food here is just amazing. The location itself is rather small but the food comes from the heart and you can taste the goodness in literally every bite. Try this place out for really good and authentic mexican cuisine
A little on the small side but great food at good prices and excellent customer service
Mixiote meat was new to me and it was bomb

Solid Mexican food, with quite the array of salsas and aji to choose from. It is tasty in all the right ways, and they give you the right choices to make (ie. Black beans are the main beans used, as they should be). Good prices, food is fresh, I can't tell you enough how much I like this place. And good selection of jarritos sodas. The options are simple but they offer exactly what an authentic Mexican place should have.
Bad service not friendly bad actitud

It's a very understated place that appears to mainly serve takeout. Not a lot seating in the restaurant. I had the burrito bowl and it had well cooked chicken, fresh ingredients. It felt like an authentic version of chipotle. Spicy salsa was a little lacking in kick for me, but overall great food.
I tried their fish taco Al pastor and it’s incredibly amazing!!! I especially like there’s pineapple in it. Great price with great portion.
Small, dirty and extremely unfriendly... Avoid at all costs...
Tried different selections of tacos. The texture and taste was not good. There are much better tacos in the area
I wish they had more vegetable on the menu, but I’m happy that they can accommodate vegans!
Great husband and wife duo. Very friendly and the food is delicious and fairly priced
😍😍😍 service and food were perfect
Amazing authentic Mexican food. Highly recommend this place for burritos and tacos.

Great authentic Mexican food for a decent price, very friendly staff! Will definitely visit again.
I love their food. You can order if youre from the area. The food is fresh ! Great taco bowls or anything mexican you need.
Delicious and inexpensive Mexican food. And you get 10% student discount. Can't recommend enough!
Food is fresh and amazing!
Great food, friendly service, wonderful owner. I've ordered both vegetarian and meat dishes and came back two days later. This will be my new Mexican food go-to.
On time food.
Awesome burrito, really good enchiladas with mole. Want to go back and try their tacos. Also had their corn/bean cake called the “burritas”, really good. Nice humble place, will be back.
I'm from California, and this is probably some of the best Mexican food I have had on this coast
Best tacos ever! And try the Burritas Frijolitos! You can't find this anywhere else it's unique to them. They have outdoor seating perfect for great weather days. The owner is pretty nice too.
Love the fish based bowls! Great quantity for the price!
Great authentic Mexican food!
Great food. I was delighted to eat their quesadillas ! So delicious :p I found their tacos poor in meat but quite good !

Best Mexican food in the area. After moving to the area from Arizona I missed good Mexican food but I found it here. I think they e gotten a lot more popular too. Delivery times have gotten slower. Still worth it.
Great food Great staff  One of the best guacamole.  Tacos are good!  Outdoor seating in summer

One of the best places in Hamilton Heights! The "Pastor" with fish and pineapples is delicious in any variation! The burritas are unique to the place and amazing! The owner is very friendly and food is always ready in just a few minutes

You will not find better, more legit homemade Mexican food with this good prices in NYC. Burritos are top notch, shout out to the Pollo asado (garlicky), off the charts Verde sauce. Quesadillas are fantastic as well and never too greasy.  Most importantly, it's a family restaurant and they treat you like part of the fam. They put love into every dish they make at reasonable prices. Guacamole is on point at half the cost you'd find elsewhere.  Totally addicted. Will support this beautiful establishment forever!
Nice authentic food. Excellent grab and go with small space for eating in.

Great spot to grab lunch on the go. Fresh ingredients packed with flavor at a decent price. Counter service is friendly and speedy.
Never thought I'd say this, but their burritos could actually benefit from being slightly smaller... Fast, polite, delicious.

I had the worst experience with the owner today regarding my grub hub delivery. He was insulting and disrespectful.  He left me feeling like he was talking to me in an abrupt and rude manner because I was a female and while he told me it would take an hour to resend the delivery because he was busy - he refused to make the food and to redeliver the food despite the fact they delivered it 30 minutes early.  Decent tacos are not worth being disrespected. He should think about how he comes across over the phone - what if it was his mother or wife on the other end of the phone. Never again.
Excellent hole in the wall, best burrito in the city. Order a burrita. Never heard of it before and it is excellent.
Great tacos 👍🏾👍🏾

Interesting place, food was very good but a bit dissappointed at the tortilla shells...not home made or at least didn't taste it and the chorizo was a bit pasty. However I liked the flavors of everything I tried and the guacamole was excellent. Their burritos are stuffed to the max!!! Excellent! I'd definitely come back here for more in the future.

Excellent chi ken enchiladas in green sauce! Perfectly spicey!  Not too spicey but definitely with a kick!  Served with true mexican rice: pink rice.  This is a tiny restaurant. Basically it is all take out here.  Cant wait to try the tacos!

The best place

This was one of the first places I came to when I moved to the neighborhood, and I loved it so much we've gone back every chance we get. The owners are wonderful and very nice, you can tell they care about the food just from the work and love they put into it.  The tacos are some of the best I've ever had, and their quesadillas are perfectly crisp. They also just got a permit for outdoor seating, so now there's plenty of space!

Authentic fresh mexican food, family own, great service. I had the chicken Torta, so many flavors yummy, best torta I've had. The traditional BURRITAS from Puebla, their native place in Mexico super yummy, a must have🤗 i recommend this place to everyone.

Simply the best carnitas bowl I have ever had. The verde hot sauce is the perfect balance of flavor and spice. The owners here are very kind and sociable. This place is amazing and help keep the small businesses alive!
I love this place. Everything is made fresh. Tacos are so good. My favorite is the hard shell chicken taco. A family business with a sense of humor.

Recently moved to the neighborhood, and it's my favorite place to eat! Eduardo is super friendly, and he makes amazing food! His burrito's are the same price as Chipotle, but you get so much more food, and it's so much better! I can't recommend Friolitos enough!

Awesome vegetarian burrito. Only concern is that there are too many burrito contents for him to wrap it up well so stuff doesn't fall out, but if you dine in, you get a fork and a bowl so it is a non problem.

Great place, great people, great food. The owners are very nice and enjoyable to interact with. The carnitas tacos are my favorite. I have only eaten in, and while it’s a small shop there have always been seats available.

Based on the other positive reviews, and my desperate need for a burrito that reminds me of my days in California, I gave Frijolito's a shot, and I'm happy to say it was a great burrito!  Big and fat and sloppy and tasty.  One thing they can do better is to have horchata - that's a great drink with a burrito.  But they have guava soda, which is pretty good too.

I found this little treasure one day, it's the best Mexican restaurant in New York City  I have ever eaten .. I tried Picante down the street they cost more & there food is not that good TRUST ME  FRIJOLITO'S IS THE BEST!!

caption: Really fresh ingredients. Al pastor tacos are DELICIOUS! Very friendly staff, good prices and fast delivery. A great addition to the neighborhood.

Great food and service. Their delivery service is superb and if you go in person they have a very warm and inviting space. I almost always get a burrito, but I think I've sampled everything else by way of stealing it off of friends plates. All of it is delicious AND FILLING. They do not skimp on portions. If I want Mexican food around home, this is where I go for it.

This is such a welcome addition to the neighborhood.  Skip the taco truck and pay a few more dollars for this fresh, homemade food.  A friendly staff and fast service are a plus.  The crispy tacos with guacamole is a guilty pleasure.

Ummm this place is unreal!!! Its so good its hard to even wrap my mind around. I cannot believe that a restaurant this small can deliver such good food. The veggie burrito and the veggie quesadillas are the best I ever ate in Manhattan. The portions are huge and the prices are super low. One burrito is probably big enough for two people of standard hungers. I get my own when I am feeling ravenous. Great place. I highly highly recommended.
